betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Getting dirt should have given you some saplings to work with.

Trees will grow faster if you "Twerk" (Crouch and Uncrouch) near em.

You also have access to OreExcavation. The default is the "Grave" key usually under the ESC button. (Listed under "Excavate" in your Controls)

Hold that while breaking a block and nearby blocks of that type will also break.
Get some Redstone Stuff

Bust out a Barrel. You can make water by collecting rain.

Make sure to set up an infinate water source.

Make a Crook with 4 sticks. (Optionally you can make a compressed Crook for more durability)

Break Leaves with the Crook to get Silkworms.

Use the worms on Leaves to make them Infested Leaves.

Breaking Infested Leaves gives you string.

Make a bed.

Too easy.
9 String makes a String Mesh.

Sieve Compressed Dirt and get stuff.

Pebbles can be turned into cobblestone

Hammers can turn:

Cobblestone into Gravel
Gravel into Sand
Sand into Dust

Put Ancient Spores on some dirt to make Mycellium.

Place a Wooden Barrel on top of the Mycellium to make Witchwater.

While the Water is turning into Witchwater it will randomly spawn mushrooms as well.

When the Witchwater is done, put a block of sand inside the Barrel to get Soulsand.
Sieve some Dust with a String Mesh
Gravel can help you make Flint. Just place a bunch on the ground and use OreExcavation to punch it. After a few attempts you should have enough flint.
With a Flint Mesh, you can sieve gravel.

Put Dust in a Barrel full of Water in order to make Clay.

Combine Clay and Bonemeal to make Porcelain Clay.

4 Pieces make a Chunk.

Smelt Chunks to make Ingots.
Sift Gravel and Dust in the Iron Mesh in order to get hot loot.

Put the Unfired Crucible into a Furnace, if you haven't already.

Put some heat under the Crucible (either some flint-n-steel fire or just a torch).

Put some Cobblestone inside the Crucible and wait for it to melt into Lava.

Click it with a bucket once it's done to get a bucket of lava.

Place Lava inside a Stone Barrel.

Pour water on top of the barrel.

Obsidian Get.
Use a Flint Mesh to sieve Soulsand

There are literally so many steps you need to get here.

Good Luck.

Anti-Grind Table. Turns items into Pure Energy called EMC, which can be recreated into any other item.

(RTC = Right Transmutation Circle)

Place the table down to start using it. It starts off with no knowledge and no EMC, so "burn" some items to gain both (shift clicking into it will default to burning the item).

Items you can request are in the RTC. Items on the outer circles are regular items and the inner circles are ProjectE fuels (redstone, charcoal, glowstone, etc)

Place it on the Left Transmutation Circle to learn without burning.

Putting an item on the book with an X will forget the item.

Placing it in the center of the RTC will "search" for that item.

Craft using a Diamond, some redstone, and some glowstone.

With the Philosopher's Stone, you can transform dirt, cobblestone, sand and grass into each other (use it while crouching as well).

You can also transmute logs and saplings into each other.

Water and Lava to and from Ice and Obsidian.

Wool and Carpet colors. Melon and Pumpkins. And so much more.
Dust Loot
Gravel Loot
Control Time like a GOD

Alchemical Chest is just a huge chest tbh.

Energy Condensers turn items with EMC into any desired item.

EMC link will link into your personal EMC table.

A good way to hook up a mob farm to your EMC supplies.
Never get hurt or get hungry ever again with these OP power stones

These bad bois make energy from like . . . the 17th dimension or something.

Either, hook em up to a Energy Condenser

or, let them collect energy and "harvest" by letting it upgrade fuels. (Check out the Collector Fuel Upgrades in JEI)

Learn how to fly.

The ring will also push mobs around like an interdiction torch.

You need to have EMC storage in your inventory in order to do either action.

Connect the EMC Collectors to EMC condensors by using these Relays.

The better the relay, the more Energy it can transfer and store if needed.
The literal definition of OP
Make Infinate Water and Lava on a whim
Keep your Transmutation table on the go

Gold is a great source of EMC.

An Early Game way to do this is to make a giant platform in the Nether. And have a safe place to attack them from.

(Remember: mobs don't spawn within 24 blocks of the player)

A MidGame way to do this is by giving a Nether Portal Extra Ticks since there's a small RNG chance for a pigman to spawn in the portal frame. Just make a place for em to fall into.

Durability is a thing of the past.
This will heal up your Tools.

Instead of making a Purely Vanilla Passive Mob Spawner, ExCompressum has many Baits (Wolf, Pig, Sheep, and Rabbit to name a few)

We will need leather and feathers eventually so we'll need Cow and Chicken Bait.

Where you place the bait defines a 5x5 area which needs certain requirements met:

- At least 10 "home enviroment" blocks (Wood, Saplings, and Grass count for most baits)
- There must be at least 1 water source
- No players
- No more than 2 animals

If it is working, there will be smoke coming off the bait (you'll need to wait about 1-3 minutes or more if you're unlucky).

Remember: You can feed baby animals to make them grow faster.
Craft a Book and a Sapling together
Get Red Yellow and White Vanilla Dyes to make Botania Bonemeal.
You'll need a Pestle and Mortar to Crunch up the Petals
Make a Fully Powered Enchantment Table
Get One of Every Petal
Get all the Mystical Botania Flowers

Get some Cobblestone and a petal to make yourself an apothecary.

Place it in the world and toss a bucket into it to fill it with water.

The Apothecary can make other flowers too. These plants will generate mana for you.

Place down the Mana Spreader pointing towards the mana pool. Next, place the flowers near the spreader (the range is more or less 6 blocks away).

Hydrogeas need a water source block near them to function.

Endoflames will eat fuel items you drop for them. Anything between just Charcoal up to entire Coal Blocks.

The Pure Daisy does what it says. Purifies Blocks like Logs and Stone (not cobblestone though).

It can even turn Water into Snow (as long as the water doesn't break the flower)

To make it toss 4 white petals into the Apothecary and then toss in a seed.
Dropping items into a mana pool will infuse the item with mana.

Put this baby under one of your mana pools so it can cycle through some items.

It can transform:
Vines -> Lilypads
Snow -> Ice
Book-n-Quills -> Nametags
Rotten Flesh -> Leather
Cactus -> Slime
AND MORE

(You can get Vines from 2x2 jungle trees and Cactus from sieving dirt)

ProjectE has upgradable fuel.

The Bottom level is coal. You can craft these by putting 4 fuels with the Philosopher's Stone.

Outputs power of 15 when it is raining and 0 any other time.

It can be inverted so it's 15 when it's not raining and is off when it is.
You can dye item frames

Craft the Storage Tablet and Module together to have portable storage and crafting. Keep in mind you'll need to charge it to keep it active.

If you don't have a power source to charge a tablet yet, you can just plonk down some Modular Storage and insert the Storage Module into that instead.
This block will store items and preform the actions you program into it

Using Dolls and Barrels, you can spawn enemies.
Kill them to get hot loot.

As the name suggests it randomizes redstone.

The input is on the front and it will randomly output between the two sides. It will randomize on every pulse and will hold signal as long as the input is on.
A Chute is like a dropper but is dropping forever. It will drop anything that goes into it perfectly down the middle.
Trowels randomly place blocks in your hotbar
You can make Carpets with leaves
Add Glowstone Dust to a Barrel of Lava to get Endstone
Use a String Mesh to sieve Soulsand
The Elves like trading, so send em some mana infused stuff once you get the portal open

Offer the Lexica Botania as Tribute to the Elves and gain Wicked Sick Knowledge

There's so much more to Botania. These were just the basics. Have fun ^u^

In the Lexica Botania, go to the bottom of Basics and Mechanics for the Terrasteel Entry.

Make a 3x3 with Lapis Blocks and Livingstone and put the Plate on top of the center.

It is reccommended that you use sparks on top of the plate and a few mana pools so mana transfer happens more quickly.

The amount of mana needed is about half of a mana pool.

In the Lexica Botania, go to Alfhomancy to view how to make the portal. The space it takes up is a vertical 5x5 not including the space for the Pylons.

You need to place the Pylons within a 9x9x9 centered on the Core and on top of mostly full Mana Pools. (That means at most 4 blocks away in any single direction)
Make some energy and then some Stoneburnt
With this magic wand you can make platforms quickly. It places multiple blocks at a time.

This loyal item will return to you once it hits something (or after a while).

It can be enchanted for more capabilities.
These are the easiest to set up. Make yourself a good power source.
Add Redstone Dust to a Barrel of Lava to get Endstone
Smelt Netherrack to get Nether Brick and Craft 4 of em together to get Nether Brick
Surround Lava with Nether Bricks and toss some gold into it. You should get demon ingots.

Use a Diamond Mesh to sieve Soulsand.

Don't be scared when it doesn't happen for a while. It has a really low rate.
You need Ghast Tears and Ender Eyes
Only eat when you're ready to fight the dragon
End Game Energy Bois

Heat Generators are the first thing to make when starting Mekanism.

Personally,, I like giving em Charcoal but any fuel will do. If it burns in a Furnace, it will probably burn here.

Need to make some Alloys to start off with Mekanism.

Place the Infuser connected to the Generator. The Infuser GUI should show it receiving energy.

Put some Redstone in the infusion compartment, it should be absorbed by the Infuser.

Put Osmium and Iron Ingots into the Infuser to make the components you need.

Generate Energy without even looking.

As expected Solar Panels won't make energy at night.

Wind Generators make more energy the higher up they are.

Transporters transfer Items
Bins can store Items in Bulk
(Or just use chests, I guess)

Making Steel is a super infusing process.

The Infusion Type is Carbon (so coal is the infusion item).

Put Iron in the Infuser to make Enriched Iron.

Put the Enriched Iron back in to get Steel Dust.

Finally, Smelt the Steel Dust to get a Steel Ingot.
You can use Energy to smelt instead of Coal

Cables transfer Energy
Cubes can store it

Pumps can slurp
Pipes transfer Fluids
Tanks can store em

Honestly the tank is pretty and has a useful GUI but most cases it would be best to use a drum instead.
The Configurator will help you set up pipes and stuff.

You can wirelessly transfer anything. Even yourself.

You need 2 Entangloporters to transfer items/fluids/etc between.

You need 2 teleporters (there is a portable version as well)
Pretty Self-Explanatory
At this point, you should be able to do this easy

Upgrade your Infuser into a Factory!

It's super useful to turn on Auto-Sorting so it splits up items evenly through the Machine.

The grass block underneath you regenerates.

There are quite a few ways to get the dirt but I reccomend Crouching on a corner while breaking it.

This lets you "glitch" through the block, stand on the dirt underneath, and break the regen dirt easily.

After you have a few dirt, it'll be best for you to make yourself a platform to actually stand on though.
Upgrade it all the way
Gotta Upgrade that Cube

Cobble + Charcoal
Iron + Redstone
Diamond + Coal

Skeletons + Witchwater = Wither Skeletons

Make a T-Shape out of Soulsand and put 3 Wither Skulls on top to summon the Wither. Wither will always drop a Star when killed.
Keep this in your inventory when fighting Wither Stuff
Activate and put this on your head
Yummy Food
Place this in the world and mobs can't get close

You can upgrade most Mekanism Machinery.

You'll need either a Crusher or an Enrichment Chamber in order to make the dusts required.
Put Osmium into an Osmium Compressor in order to turn Obsidian and Glowstone into ingots

Redstone, Coal, Diamonds, and Obsidian will be transformed in this Meka Machine.

The compressed will give 2x more infusion in a Infusion Machine.

Chorus Fruit can only be found in the end.

In order to get to a place in the end with fruit you have to ender pearl through the portals that appear after the Dragon has been beaten.

Sometimes you need more info about mana inside your pools and/or need more control into the flow of the mana around you.

This Wand can rebind flowers to different spreaders. Orient Spreaders in all directions. Display information. And much more.

Crouch clicking is how you rebind spreaders and flowers to point in different directions. Regular clicking will simply refresh the info displays.

There's lots of ways to use chisel and bits.

Bits can prevent water flows.

Enough Glowstone bits as part of a block will create light level 15.

It's great decoration but a bit of a rabbit hole. 
The default control for the radial menu is LMENU.
Go Ham, M8.
iChisel makes chiseling more easy
Chiselling blocks makes them pretty
Powerful Mesh is Powerful

Sieving Sand with a Diamond Mesh will get you Prismarine Shards.

Don't be scared when it doesn't happen for a while. It has a really low rate.

Put a Mana Spreader adjacent to a Mana Pool pointing towards the Runic Altar.

With the runic altar, you can create runes which are useful for later crafting.

Toss items on top of the Altar and the Mana Spreader will start charging the Altar.

When it is done charging, toss a Livingrock on top and use the Wand to imprint the rock with the mana and items and thus create a Rune.

Great way to move Items and Fluids around. As well as Filtering only the items you need to move around.

If you want to upgrade it to move faster, you'll need to keep up the RF energy demand.
One of the best early game foods
Getting water can be done using a Wooden Crucible. Just put some organics inside
